$CMCSA & $CHTR in new 50-50 JV, which will include Comcast’s Xfinity Flex streaming platform, its HiSense-manufactured XClass TVs, its ad-supported Xumo streaming service, & NBC’s Peacock. Charter (which operates under the Spectrum brand) will invest $900M & access to its roughly 32M subs in 41 states. 
 
The new partnership will see Comcast’s XClass 4K TVs, which are powered by Comcast’s Flex streaming operating system made available “through national retail partners” & “potentially” Comcast and& Charter themselves. 
 
Charter, meanwhile, will begin offering Comcast’s Flex streaming devices & voice remotes as soon as next year. 
 
eMarketer: $ROKU remains the top CTV platform in the US, accounting for 51.7% of CTV users. But $AMZN Fire TV is much closer now with a penetration rate of nearly 45% among CTV users. $AAPL TV's penetration is pretty low compared with the rest, at only 13.1% of US CTV users.
